{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/how-to-make-a-virtual-die-roller","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"what-is-random\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-is-random\" aria-label=\"what is random permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is random?</h2>\n<p>Random is a python package that comes pre-installed when you install Python. It is a way to generate pseudo-random numbers that can be used in many different ways.</p>\n<h2 id=\"making-our-virtual-die\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#making-our-virtual-die\" aria-label=\"making our virtual die permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Making our virtual die</h2>\n<p>First off, we need to import the package like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> random</code></pre></div>\n<p>Since a normal die has six sides we want to pick a random number 1-6. We can do that like so:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> random\n\nresult <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> random<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>randint<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">random.randint(1,6)</code> chooses 1-6 at random and stores it in our variable I called <code class=\"language-text\">result</code>.</p>\n<p>Now we want to print our result to the console. We can do that by typing this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"python\"><pre class=\"language-python\"><code class=\"language-python\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> random\n\nresult <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> random<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>randint<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">print</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string-interpolation\"><span class=\"token string\">f'You rolled a </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">!'</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token builtin\">input</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Press enter to continue...\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>I now have added a way to print our result and I put the variable in an f-string so that I can add my value inside the string. I also added an input to prevent the console from closing immediately after running and a way to exit the program.</p>\n<p>Thats it! You now have a virtual die!</p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"What is random? Random is a python package that comes pre-installed when you install Python. It is a way to generate pseudo-random numbers…","frontmatter":{"title":"How to make a virtual die roller","date":"2020-10-23 15:41:42 -0700","categories":["python"],"tags":["python","random","beginner"],"description":null,"keywords":"python, random, beginner","author":"William Dessert","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":204,"height":132,"src":"/static/c4fa3c5851be4bf4f2f39daf2e691d3b/02521/python.png","srcSet":"/static/c4fa3c5851be4bf4f2f39daf2e691d3b/02521/python.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-make-a-virtual-die-roller","date":"2020-10-23T22:41:42.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/how-to-make-a-virtual-die-roller","nexttitle":"Java Collection Hierarchy","nextslug":"/java-collection-hierarchy","prevtitle":"Controller vs RestController in Spring Boot","prevslug":"/controller-vs-restcontroller-in-spring-boot","tagList":["java","interface","callbacks","asynchronus calls","python","pandas","abstraction","OOP","Class","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structure","optimization","java 7","Java 8","comparison","mkdir(make-dir) and rmdir(remove-dir command) command","nodejs","backend","frontend","postgres","mac","installation","games","gamedev","memory","html","bootstrap","web development","da